    • Constructor Detail

      • Statement1Visitor

        public Statement1Visitor(org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.CompilationUnit compilationUnit,
                 java.util.Map<java.lang.String,Variable> variables,
                 java.util.List<IfElseBranch> conditions,
                 boolean isDeadCode,
                 java.util.List<IfElseBranch> previousIfElseBranch,
                 java.util.List<ForLoop> loops,
                 int nestingLevel)
        This class will parse a statement and (if it is a IF) will also parse recursively the IF-ELSE blocks.
        Parameters:
        compilationUnit - The compilation unit. Can be used to print useful information (source line)
        variables - the already encounterd variables of the code
        conditions - the previously IF-ELSE branches we entered before to get here
        isDeadCode - a boolean variable stating if this code is dead (not reachable) TODO: to be checked if the implementation is ok
        previousIfElseBranch - the previously seen IF-ELSE statements (encountered but NOT entered in)
        loops - the loops we entered in to get here
        nestingLevel - the current nesting level (if this is an IF inside an IF, then the nestingLevel is 2).
